ratings.rComments: She was extremely specific about everything and don't even bother asking questions because she'll refer you to the syllabus every time. The PBL's took me HOURS upon HOURS. But! Extra credit is a thing in this class and take advantage of it.

Every comment mentioning how condescending and rude she is? It's true.  I've never even met her in real life, but her few e-mails seep of how self-absorbed. She doesn't even give actual lectures, yet she still complains about how many students take this course. Half the online lectures are done by another professor!  Still an easy A, though.

What a poor excuse for a professor. Extra Credit sessions were basically "office hours" where she complains about how no one pays attention to her during lectures in the past. She cares nothing about the student and only enjoys talking about herself. No sympathy when emergencies occur. Please fire her and avoid her at all costs.
Easy A Gen Ed Course. Very little homework or exams. Highly Recommended.
Going to the class was not helpful at all. All the work is online and powerpoints and quizzes are more confusing than they need to be. I think this class could have been much more interesting.

The thing is that you never actually see in her in person. This class is taught by a UM and is very easy if you stay on top of all the homework and don't miss assignments. class is once a week and you can miss 2 so it's not a problem at all

This class was stupid.Attendance was mandatory, but we rarely talked about anything useful. Everything else was online. Don't get me wrong this class was EASY. I got an A. But it required A LOT of reading & taking notes on 3-5 lessons/readings PER WEEK. & just when you decide to stop taking notes, she quizzes you on them. So take good notes.
It's an easy class if you do all of your assignments and go to the one hour discussion section once a week.

To be honest, the class was really easy. As many earlier comments have mentioned, do all the assignments carefully and an A is guaranteed. The content is interesting and the course is very well outlined. However, the course seems very under-staffed. Assignments were graded weeks after the deadline, as there were 4 TA's (graders) and 750 students.

The class is very easy, its online so not much work. Do the assignmenst and you are sure to recieve an A! I liked the way the class was handled except the material was boring. Take it for an easy A. Oh and no exams so thats a definite plus, only projects which are not hard at all.

DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS. Although it's blended and you barely see the professor she still manages to be extremely rude to her students.  She literally should be fired from this university for her unwillingness to discuss things with her students. She acts like it's a burden for her to teach you and you should bow down tot her greatness.

Where do I begin? Honestly if you are taking the blended version of online and discussion, dont even think about it. I wanted to take this course thinking of minoring in anthro... this teacher completely swayed me the other way... The online stuff is so much reading and then the discussion has nothing to do with the material.. Dont take this class

This is the worst class I've taken. It's too bad because it is such an interesting subject. Discussion and the online portion don't really relate to each other. The professor talks down to you and sends a lot of negative emails/feedback. DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS

yeah..."You don't get it for just showing up. If you are belligerent or have no question, no points...But if you find this class a breeze and are getting an A+ or something, and you think you are just too darn good for office hours... it's ok if you don't clog the line and don't come. You likely don't need the points."

LOVED this course. Going in, I barely knew what anthropology was. The blended course was fantastic. GO TO LECTURE. It's only once a week after all, but because of this: GO TO OFFICE HOURS. The UM's and TA's are fantastic. Prof. Clancy is very approachable and knowledgeable.

Where do I begin? Clancy has a ridiculously condescending demeanor. It's a shame, because the subject matter is so interesting. She simply treats you like a five year old, regardless of your age or experiences. Clancy loves to talk about herself and her children. Easy A, but at the cost of wasted time and money. Lecture is worthless.
easiest A of my life. just show up and zone out to do the i-clicker questions. do the online assignments on time and you'll be fine.

Clancy was extremely intelligent, interesting, and extraordinarily organized, but was also extremely unhelpful, irritating, and arrogant.  She made the class seem so hard, but it was a piece of cake.  The class seemed more about monkeys than humans, but there were still some very interesting lectures.  Take it for an easy A.

My favorite class! I learned so much in this class and found interest in it because of her great teaching methods. Everything was online and we had lecture once a week. Since it is a huge lecture of 600+ it was intimidating; however, the UM's and TA's are extremely helpful and friendly!keep up with the work and attend office hours. I got an A :)
Class is very easy but you need to show up. No exams which is great but at times there is a lot of work.

I took this class (Biology of Human Behavior) because it sounded very interesting. Professor Clancy somehow manages to make every class extremely boring. She loves to hear herself speak, treats students like children, and is overwhelmingly feminist. Luckily, this years class has no tests (only projects) and is half online

Looooves to hear herself talk. Makes a big deal about being 'professor clancy' while she is an assistant.  Really disconnected and most of her rants are about how you should under no circumstances attempt to contact her or email her because her time is too precious for students
very dedicated and knowledgeable teacher, expected a lot but definitely knew what she was talking about

You have to go to class to get your iClicker points, however they aren't worth much of your grade... so if you have a high A don't bother! She is kind of a snobby teacher, but the class is interesting and has reasonable expectations!

Definitely the worst gen-ed teacher at the U of I. She thinks she's God's gift to mankind by taking part in rallies, etc. The material is very interesting, but she just makes the class a tad too(x100) boring. She treats you like a child. And she is weirdly obsessed with cats and her daughter( though the latter is cute).avoid this class if possible.

The material is very interesting and the readings aren't as bad as people say.  She, however, is pretty unhelpful.  I saw her during office hours and that was a truly intimidating experience and even though I saw she was on Facebook, when I walked in she tried her hardest to get me out...quickly.

Managed to keep lecture in check, clearly very invested in materials she teaches, and material had refreshing women's studies slant. She's not "borderline" feminist. She IS feminist. Great class. Loved her.

Caring, kind prof. She cares about each student. She calls out students so that the ones who actually CARE about the class can hear and learn. She is not the LEAST bit mean. She is approachable, kind, and helpful. If you're confused about something, go to her office hours. She is incredibly helpful and tries way more than most profs.

Easy to get A/B, but not a blowoff class. Notes are online but very hard to follow if you dont go to lecture. She uses iClicker for points everyday. quizzes are worded weirdly sometimes, and she takes content from readings and class.  Tests were pretty reasonable, and take advantage of extra credit! good teacher, but as a person a little pushy
It was refreshing to have a professor who was clearly well educated and passionate about what she was teaching for a gen ed class. Interesting material from an expert, do take.

She is really full of herself and is borderline feminist. Lectures can be at times interesting, but not mandatory. Intelligent in area to some extent, but can say some pretty disagreeable things, especially to men. Her LOLcats are ridiculous and distractingly unfunny.

She is really mean and is not afraid to call you out for talking in a 700-person lecture hall. She is passionate and knowledgeable in her subject area, though. And she wears really cute clothes. The class is definitely interesting.

Clancy doesn't seem to care if you pass or fail her class. She's just there to hear herself talk. She won't answer any student's questions, you have to email a faceless TA (I say faceless b/c you see them once at the beginning of the semester when she introduces them and never again). This class was way hard for just a gen ed.

Attendance to lectures is not mandatory but you will be LOST if you don't go, not a blow-off. A majority of the questions on the exams are from the online quizzes to try to do well and study those.  If you don't have to take the class, don't! Not an easy gen-ed and very boring unless you are really interested in monkeys!!
She always tells us to shut up and it's annoying

She is passionate about what she does, and tries to make the class interesting. However she has a chip on her shoulder and it shows she has a need for everyone to pay attention to her. Lectures are in general useless and the quizzes are not from lecture or reading at times. Tests are fair.

She is one of the best professors I've had.  She makes everything easy to understand, and I came away learning a lot.  The exams were easy.  You can tell that she is very passionate about what she does.  I'd love to take another class with her.
incredibly intelligent, funny, and nice woman.  she made this class highly relevant and interesting.  go to class, and the material will stick.
Go to class; you get to see her and learn something.

This huge lecture class made Professor Clancy only care about her Honors Section rather the rest of the 600 students.  She provides all of the lecture notes online, so you would only need to report to the lectures three times for the three exams.  Also, 6 easy online quizzes are added to your grade.

Despite what others have put here, she DOES post lecture notes online. Most probably cannot get to them because they are posted close to the beginning of class. 6 quizzes(all open note), 3 exams(all with a TA-led study session), NO final, NO textbook.
She was a really amazing professor. Class is interesting even in Foellinger, but she does lecture a little fast. She's amusing and also very knowledgeable about the topics in class.

There is NO: book, study guide, extra credit, exception with quizzes. Rushes through material, won't post slides b/4 class. The test were :|. Lectures could've been better. She doesn't want students to email her, if u do she will send email to TA, mail u back to tell u that, when she could have just answered the quest. Hard for gen ed.

Her lectures are really boring. And those LOL cats are ridiculous - just a waste of paper. She is most definitely full of herself - brags about how smart she is. Doesn't offer any extra credit. Her exams aren't too hard, but some of her questions are like those "A and B, but not C, or maybe D." Oh yeah, I missed an A- by .01. She won't budge.

Easy class. No textbook. But she doesn't post notes before class, so you either scribble through class or can just listen and print notes later. Interesting lecture--adds LOLCats and funny stories. Keeps lecture really open to discussion. TIP: Slides that have questions on them--write the answers to! These are the types of things on the tests
She got me really intrigued with Anth.  She kept the lecture open for discussions, which was nice.  Really neat material.

I took this class as a gen. ed. and it ended up not being that bad. She posts all of her notes online so I don't even go to lecture. No papers or anything, just 3 midterms. Class itself is kind of boring, but some of the info can be interesting. All in all I would recommend to someone looking for an easy A-B.

She talks way too fast and you can't get down all of what she says, but she doesn't like to put the lecture notes online before class. She also thinks LOLcats are really funny and wastes people's time by adding them into lectures. Don't take this class unless you have to. It's not too hard but its super boring and she's really full of herself.
No Comments
